  <!-- MOTION SENSOR SECURITY LIGHTS -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Motion Sensor Security Lights</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Motion sensor security lights are a highly effective addition to any security lighting setup. These lights use built-in motion sensors to detect movement, automatically illuminating the area when someone approaches. This feature not only conserves energy—since the lights are only on when needed—but also provides an immediate visual deterrent to potential intruders.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Motion sensor security lights come in a variety of styles, including powerful floodlights for large areas, focused spotlights for pathways, and decorative options for gardens. When installing motion sensor security lights, consider the detection range, sensitivity, and duration settings to tailor the system to your property's unique needs. Properly positioned motion sensor security lights can help detect movement around your home or business, making it much harder for intruders to approach unnoticed. For the best results, have your motion sensor security lights installed by a professional to ensure optimal coverage and reliable operation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LED LIGHTS FOR SECURITY -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">LED Lights for Security</h2>
        <p class="mb-6">
          LED lights are a top choice for security lighting thanks to their energy efficiency, long lifespan, and powerful illumination. Security lights using LED technology are available in a range of options, including motion activated lights, floodlights, and even solar powered lights for areas without easy access to mains power. LED security lights are ideal for outdoor use, as they are designed to withstand harsh weather conditions and provide consistent, bright lighting year-round.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          Choosing LED lights for your security lighting system means you benefit from lower energy costs and reduced maintenance, as LEDs last significantly longer than traditional bulbs. When selecting LED security lights, pay attention to the lumens (brightness), color temperature (for visibility and comfort), and IP rating (for weather resistance). Whether you need solar powered lights for remote garden areas or high-output floodlights for driveways, LED lights offer a reliable and environmentally friendly solution for keeping your property secure.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <Image src={seoImg} alt="LED Security Lights" class="rounded-[35px]" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
